<h1>Abstract</h1>
	<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esports"><b>E-sports</b></a>(also known as electronic sports, e-sports, or eSports) is a form of sport competition using video games. Esports often takes the form of organized, multiplayer video game competitions, particularly between professional players, individually or as teams.</p>
	<p>eSports are video games. The difference is that participants treat these as professional sports. Players can earn a significant amount of money. They gain massive sponsorship deals thanks to their large fan followings. There are large tournament payouts.</p>
	<p>The website offer eSports related news, furthermore, they prominently display tournament schedules.  The website is simple to use since they provide easy instructions for users. It’s easy to find player ranking, tournament results, and statistics.</p>
	<p>Users can find tournaments for games they love, furthermore, organizing tournaments is possible too. This website acts as a platform that allows game publishers to form communities, organizers of eSports tournaments covering All major eSports games and covering all regions.</p>
